"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Fix: Switch Kiro E2E to `--no-interactive` mode\n\n## Context\n\nKiro E2E tests fail in CI with \"You are not logged in\" because kiro-cli's **interactive TUI doesn't support SIGV4 env-var auth**. The `setup-kiro-action` reference confirms SIGV4 is designed for `--no-interactive` only ‚Äî all CI examples use it.\n\n**Verified:** `--no-interactive` **fires hooks** (the comment at `kiro.go:127` was wrong):\n```\n‚úì 1 of 1 hooks finished in 0.09 s  (√ó3 hooks)\n```\n\n## Changes\n\n### File: `e2e/agents/kiro.go` (only file modified)\n\n#### 1. Rewrite `RunPrompt` ‚Äî pipe-based `--no-interactive` (no tmux)\n\nModel after Claude's `RunPrompt` (`e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170`). Uses `exec.CommandContext` with stdout/stderr pipes. Env vars (SIGV4) propagate naturally ‚Äî no `env` wrapper needed.\n\n```go\nfunc (k *Kiro) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\n    // ...config setup...\n    args := []string{\"chat\", \"--no-interactive\", \"--trust-all-tools\", \"--agent\", \"entire\", prompt}\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(cmdCtx, k.Binary(), args...)\n    cmd.Dir = dir\n    cmd.Stdout = &stdout\n    cmd.Stderr = &stderr\n    err := cmd.Run()\n    // ...collect exit code and return Output...\n}\n```\n\n**Open questions to verify during implementation:**\n- Exact flag: `--trust-all-tools` (from error message) ‚Äî check `kiro-cli chat --help`\n- Prompt passing: positional arg (user's test) vs `-p` flag\n\n#### 2. Rewrite `StartSession` ‚Äî sequential `--no-interactive` commands\n\nSince interactive mode doesn't work with SIGV4, implement `Session` as a wrapper that runs a new `--no-interactive` command per `Send()`. This is the same approach the `setup-kiro-action` uses (all examples are single-shot `--no-interactive` calls).\n\n```go\ntype KiroSession struct {\n    kiro       *Kiro\n    dir        string\n    ctx        context.Context\n    lastOutput string  // captured output from most recent Send\n}\n\nfunc (k *Kiro) StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error) {\n    return &KiroSession{kiro: k, dir: dir, ctx: ctx}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Send(input string) error {\n    out, err := s.kiro.RunPrompt(s.ctx, s.dir, input)\n    s.lastOutput = out.Stdout + out.Stderr\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc (s *KiroSession) WaitFor(_ string, _ time.Duration) (string, error) {\n    return s.lastOutput, nil  // command already completed in Send\n}\n\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Capture() string { return s.lastOutput }\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Close() error    { return nil }\n```\n\n**Session interface** (`e2e/agents/agent.go:57-62`): `Send`, `WaitFor`, `Capture`, `Close`\n\n**Trade-off:** Each `Send` creates a separate kiro-cli process (separate agent-spawn/stop hooks). Multi-turn tests will exercise multiple single-turn sessions instead of one continuous session. This is acceptable because:\n- Hooks still fire correctly per prompt\n- File changes persist (same working directory)\n- The alternative (interactive TUI) doesn't work with SIGV4 at all\n- Single-turn is how `setup-kiro-action` uses kiro-cli in CI\n\n#### 3. Remove dead code\n- Delete `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` helper (no longer needed without tmux)\n- Delete incorrect comment about `--no-interactive` not firing hooks\n- Remove the old `KiroSession` struct that wrapped `TmuxSession`\n\n#### 4. Adjust imports\n- Keep: `context`, `encoding/json`, `errors`, `fmt`, `os`, `os/exec`, `strings`, `time`\n- Remove if no longer used: any tmux-only imports\n\n## What stays the same\n- `Bootstrap()` ‚Äî validates SIGV4 env vars in CI (unchanged)\n- Hook installation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/`) ‚Äî unchanged\n- CI workflows (`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`) ‚Äî unchanged\n- All other agent implementations ‚Äî unchanged\n\n## Verification\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\n2. CI E2E with `--agent kiro` should pass\n\n## Key files\n- `e2e/agents/kiro.go` ‚Äî only file modified\n- `e2e